text: Val-d'Étangson is a commune. It is found in the Pays de la Loire region in the Sarthe department in the west of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Évaillé (the seat) and Sainte-Osmane.Arrêté préfectoral 13 September 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Sarthe
title: Val-d'Étangson
